    <h3>3. The Purpose of Priority</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>Improved Response Efficiency</strong><br />
        High-priority issues are addressed first, preventing prolonged disruptions to critical business services.
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>Rational Resource Allocation</strong><br />
        Support personnel and technical resources are assigned dynamically according to priority, minimizing waste.
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>Enhanced User Trust</strong><br />
        A transparent, visible priority mechanism increases confidence and satisfaction with IT services.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h3>4. Practical Recommendations</h3>
    <p><strong>Auto-Assign Priority</strong>: Use rules in the ticketing system to automatically determine priority based on impact and urgency.</p>
    <p><strong>Support Manual Adjustment</strong>: Allow human intervention for special cases to ensure flexibility.</p>
    <p><strong>Color-Based Identification</strong>: Use color indicators in ticket lists and dashboards to enhance visibility and facilitate faster response.</p>

